{"title": "The Day of Reckoning", "content": "\"It's been a long journey and no one is coming out without scars. But it all comes down to this moment. We win or lose it all in the next few minutes. Make me proud. Make yourselves proud.\"\n\nThere are tons of dark prophecies of doomsdays and master plans that take a long time to put into action. The Day of Reckoning is the day that all the prophecies speak of... the day that the Evil Overlord wins, goodness and mercy are overthrown, and a new Dark Age arises on Earth...\n\nAt least, until the hero shows up, defeats the villain, saves the day, and returns everything to normal (usually with one or two characters sacrificing themselves to do it). This trope is about the final confrontation between the heroes and the coming evil. The long-awaited and foretold apocalypse. When the heroes finally get out from under the Darkest Hour and put a stop to the villain's plan for world domination.\n\nA specific type of story Climax. See also Darkest Hour and Final Battle.\n\nAnd nope, this trope has nothing to do with Universal Soldier: Day of Reckoning despite its title.", "url": "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheDayOfReckoning", "media_links": ["/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/MassEffect2", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/UniversalSoldierDayOfReckoning", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/PuellaMagiMadokaMagica", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/DigimonAdventure", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/FullmetalAlchemist", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Franchise/GreenLantern", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/BlackestNight", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Franchise/StarWars", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/RevengeOfTheSith", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/StarTrek2009", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/Ghostbusters1984", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/TheHobbit", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/TheLordOfTheRings", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/HarryPotterAndTheDeathlyHallows", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/DreamOfTheRood", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/WarriorCats", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literatu